//////
package.json
> entry point to the ap
> meta data (version,description,details)
> All the packages we are using
> Script(start,test)

/// step to generate package.json
* NodeJs must be installed in your laptop
> open the terminal/cmd and go inside the folder
> npm init
> Answer all questions
> Type Yes

/// step to install package
* NodeJs must be installed in your laptop
> open the terminal/cmd and go inside the folder
> npm i package / npm install package

> Local Dependency
* Local to the folder
* used for the one application only
* Added to package.json
* npm i packagename

> Dev Dependency
* Only require at the time development
* Added to package.json
* npm i --save-dev packagename

> global Dependecy
* Installed in your laptop
* Can be used for any application
* Need admin access to install
* Not added in the package.json
* Only used for running or generating the application

/// Step to install global Dependecy
# window
* open the cmd as admin
* npm i -g packagename
> npm i -g nodemon

#mac/linux
* open terminal
* sudo npm i -g packagename
> sudo npm i -g nodemon

Ecma Script > Standard of javascript
es5

function add(a,b){
    return a+b
}

es6
const add = (a,b) => { return a+b}
/////////////////////////////////////

var a = 10
var a; // declare
a = 10 // assignment

var > we can redclare and reassign
let > we cannot redclare but can reassign
const > we cannot redclare nor reassign

> var a = 10
undefined
> a
10
> var a = 20
undefined
> a
20
> a = 30
30
> a
30
> let b = 10
undefined
> b
10
> let b = 11
Uncaught SyntaxError: Identifier 'b' has already been declared
> b = 11
11
> const c = 10
undefined
> c
10
> const c = 11
Uncaught SyntaxError: Identifier 'c' has already been declared
> c = 11
Uncaught TypeError: Assignment to constant variable.


nodemon


Param
> What we pass after /
> We need to define in route
QueryParams
> What we pass after ?
> No Need to define

//es5
var a = 10
var b = "my age is "+a
"my age is 10"

//es6
let a = 10;
let b = `my age is ${a}`
"my age is 10"


